bug.short_desc: Enabling and disabling Bookmarks Toolbar causes painting issues while viewing an inline PDF

assigned_to.name: Nobody; OK to take it and work on it

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 524162 screenshot
Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:2.2a1pre) Gecko/20110405 Firefox/4.2a1pre
Enabling and disabling Bookmarks Toolbar causes painting issues while viewing an inline PDF.
Steps to reproduce:
1.Enable or install Adobe Acrobat 10 from Add-ons menu 2.Open any .PDF document in the browser 3.Adobe Reader Toolbar has to be enabled 4.Enable and disable the Bookmarks Toolbar
Actual result: After step 4, you will see the painting issue (see screenshot), the Bookmarks Toolbar is doubled and it's showing over the Adobe Reader Toolbar.
Expected results: The Bookmarks Toolbar should not have been doubled over the Adobe Toolbar.
